author: gdaniels
msg: Next step towards full doc/lit support - respect document-style services
when serializing.

author: scheu
msg: The following changes are made:
* Changed WSDL2Java so that it no longer generates a full constructor
for bean classes.
* Changed testcases that relied on this non-supported api.

author: rsitze
msg: Replaced (most) calls of form e.printStackTrace with log.error(someMessage, e)

author: scheu
msg: The following changes were made:
* Changed the comprehensive and roundtrip tests to test the
new complexType attribute support (Thanks Tom and Glen)
* Changed BeanSerializer/BeanDeserializer to use the new attribute
serialization for soap encoding.
* Fixed bug with BeanSerializer/Types related to the generation of the
attribute element in the wsdl file (...the code was generating
<element ...> instead of <attribute ...>)
* Other minor changes
